# Allowlist approach: ignore everything, then explicitly allow tracked files.
#
# Claude Code creates runtime/private state in this directory (transcripts,
# history, caches, telemetry, tokens), so a default-deny is safer.

*

# Re-include the config directory entries themselves. Per gitignore rules, a
# file cannot be re-included if its parent directory is excluded — so without
# these, none of the `!...` re-includes below would take effect on files
# inside these dirs. Listing each dir explicitly (rather than `!*/`) keeps
# runtime dirs like cache/, projects/, sessions/, telemetry/ excluded.
!agents/
!commands/
!hooks/
!skills/
!output-styles/
!plugins/
!plugins/marketplaces/

# Tracked top-level config files.
!.gitignore
!settings.json
!*.md

# .keep markers so otherwise-empty config directories get committed. `**`
# matches at any depth, covering both e.g. agents/.keep and the nested
# plugins/marketplaces/.keep.
!**/.keep

# Re-include arbitrary file contents inside the config directories. The
# directory un-ignores above only re-include the directory entries — files
# inside still match `*` on line 6 and stay ignored without these patterns.
# Together with the dir un-ignores, this means: drop a file into any of these
# dirs and it'll be tracked; drop one into cache/ or sessions/ and it won't.
!agents/*
!commands/*
!hooks/*
!skills/*
!output-styles/*
